com.swirl

Class ContentManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.swirl.Manager
      • com.swirl.ContentManager

  • public class ContentManager
extends Manager
    The ContentManager requests Content from the platform (through the API) in response to events generated by the VisitManager. It is responsible for generating operating system Notifications where appropriate (depending upon Settings) and for generating log events to reflect user and application behavior with respect to the Notifications and any presented Content.

        public ContentView getContentView()
        Returns the default ContentView. If you want to customize the look and feel or behavior you can override this method and return a subclass of ContentView that you create. The default implementation does this: 
             
      public ContentView getContentView() {
          return (contentView != null ? contentView : (contentView = new ContentView(context)));
      }
        Returns:
        an instance of ContentView or subclass

      • shouldStartContentURLActivity

        protected boolean shouldStartContentURLActivity(Content content,
                                                android.content.Intent intent)
        Called before CONTENT_TYPE_URL content is activated. If override, provides an opportunity for the subclass to accept, reject or alter the intent. The default behavior is to call startActivity with the intent passed.
        Parameters:
        content - The content containing the URL and fallbackURL
        intent - An intent based on that content
        Returns:
        true to open the content, false to stop the process, default is true

      • shouldStartContentViewActivity

        protected boolean shouldStartContentViewActivity(Content content,
                                                 android.content.Intent intent)
        Called before CONTENT_TYPE_SWIRL content is activated. If override, provides an opportunity for the subclass to accept, reject or alter the intent. The default behavior is to call startActivity with the intent passed.
        Parameters:
        content - The content containing an URL to a html interstitial
        intent - An intent based on that content
        Returns:
        true to open the content, false to stop the process, default is true

      • startContentViewActivity

        public void startContentViewActivity()
        Forces the a call to startActivity on the ContentActivity. This is used by an application to show the content window without regard to any proximity triggers.

      • shouldNotifyForContent

        protected boolean shouldNotifyForContent(Content content,
                                         android.app.Notification notification)
        Called before a notification is presented. Subclasses that override this method can accept, reject or modify the notification before display.
        Parameters:
        content - The content containing an URL to a html interstitial
        notification - The notification constructed from the content.
        Returns:
        true show the notification, false to reject it

      • requestContentPreview

        public void requestContentPreview(java.lang.String previewCode,
                                  com.swirl.Completion completion)
        Force a request for content with a preview code. Used for previewing a creative on the mobile device. If content is returned, the normal receive content process is followed which will result in an interstitial view. In either case, the completion (if provided) is called with an error or 0 if no error.
        Parameters:
        previewCode - preview code retrieved from the platform
        completion - optional completion that is called when the content request completes.
